<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,581,967]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,741,767]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head rather deep and downward inflected with poorly ossified opercular bones, anterior gill arch with 12–19 developed rakers on lower arm; 7–10 scales in an oblique row between origin of dorsal fin and lateral line.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
